The paper proposes a defense model for neural networks against adversarial examples by training the classifier into a human-perception classification model with shape preference. This involves the use of a texture transfer network and a generative adversarial network. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques, and also involves artificial intelligence (AI) and cryptography (CR) concepts. Additionally, the use of GANs suggests a possible connection to neural networks (NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.NE.
